   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since January 2012, persistent and unprecedented rains resulted in massive flooding in Colombia affecting over three million people. With a second winter rainy season wreaking havoc at a time when many areas had not yet recovered from the last season&#x2019;s devastating floods, over three million people were affected, 500,000 of whom already displaced by conflict. JOAC awarded Christian Aid &#xA3;30,000 for emergency food and non-food relief packs to approximately 3,000 people.</narrative>
  </description>
